SENATE BILL 1621
By Briggs
HOUSE BILL 1653
By Eldridge
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4 and
Title 71, relative to the department of human
services.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 71, Chapter 1, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) The general assembly finds and declares that:
(1) Access to the printed word is a fundamental prerequisite to education,
employment, and economic independence for blind persons in this state;
(2) For more than two (2) decades, accessible information services,
including the National Federation of the Blind newsline, have been supported in
this state as part of vocational rehabilitation services and have contributed
directly to the employment, job retention, long-term economic independence, and
informed participation in civic life of blind persons in this state; and
(3) Disruptions in funding for these services have resulted from
administrative inconsistency and loss of institutional knowledge.
(b) It is the intent of the general assembly to restore clarity, stability, and
accountability in providing accessible information services to blind persons in this state.
(c) The department, through the vocational rehabilitation program, shall ensure
continued access to accessible information services for blind persons in this state, which
includes the National Federation of the Blind newsline, as part of the department's
vocational rehabilitation services.
