(d) For the purpose of supporting accessible information services for blind
persons in this state, it is the legislative intent that the department, through the
vocational rehabilitation program, allocate a minimum of sixteen thousand dollars
($16,000) annually in vocational rehabilitation funds. If the department allocates such
funds, then the funds must be used to draw down available federal vocational
rehabilitation matching funds.
(e) Funds allocated pursuant to this section may be used:
(1) To maintain access to accessible information services; and
(2) To support outreach, training, and marketing activities designed to
increase utilization of vocational rehabilitation services for employment and
education-related purposes. These activities may include consumer education,
emergency services, employer-related outreach, and assistance to vocational
rehabilitation clients in using accessible information tools to seek and retain
employment.
(f) The department shall maintain documentation of funding sources related to
accessible information services funded pursuant to this section.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring it.
